Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot{} of @salt{to taste} water for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} into 2cm chunks.

Strip the leafy part of the @kale{80%g} from the stem. Tear into small pieces. Discard the stem.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water.

Cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}. Add the kale in the final 2-3 mins of cooking time.

Drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Mash together with a knob of @butter{to taste%knob} and a splash of @?milk{to taste%splash} or @water{to taste%splash}.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, mix the @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, 2 tbsp water and @salt{¼%tsp} (double both for 4p).

Add the @Irish Pork Mince{240%g} and garlic. Season with @pepper{to taste} and mix together by hand.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, 3-4 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the meatballs have cooked for ~{10%minutes}, place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Cook the @peas{120%g} for ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Once the meatballs are done, return the pan to medium-high heat. Add the meatballs, @Ballymaloe Tomato Relish{2%pot}, a knob of @butter{to taste%knob} and 25ml water (double for 4p). Coat the meatballs in the sauce.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the colcannon between plates and top with glazed meatballs.

Serve the peas alongside.